The Cape Town Cycle Tour, which this year attracted more than 35,000 entries, is a sporting event icon, not only in this country but also globally, because it is the largest timed cycle race in the world. Not all of the participants would worry the competitors in the Tour de France and it is that wide range of abilities – from top race cyclist to weekend wanderer – which is the essence of the event. It is for everybody. The scale of the numbers also shows that cycling is a flourishing sport, and activity, right around the country. That is...